    "overview": "Firefox DOM event dispatch follows a strict pipeline: a platform widget event enters through PresShell, is pre-processed by EventStateManager, then EventDispatcher builds the event-target chain by walking GetEventTargetParent() up the DOM, runs capture/bubble traversal via HandleEventTargetChain(), invokes listeners through EventListenerManager, and finally executes default/activation behavior.",
