      {
        "stage": 1,
        "name": "Widget-to-DOM Bridge",
        "description": "A native OS/widget event (WidgetGUIEvent) arrives at the presentation shell. PresShell::HandleEvent() is the single entry point that receives the raw widget event, performs hit-testing to find the deepest frame under the pointer, resolves the DOM content node for that frame, and then orchestrates the three-phase pipeline (PreHandle → DOM dispatch → PostHandle).",
