      },
      {
        "stage": 3,
        "name": "Event Object Creation",
        "description": "WidgetEvent (the internal C++ struct) is wrapped in a DOM-facing dom::Event object. EventDispatcher::CreateEvent() is the factory: it switches on the WidgetEvent's mClass to instantiate the correct subclass (MouseEvent, KeyboardEvent, PointerEvent, etc.). The dom::Event constructor calls ConstructorInit(), which stores the WidgetEvent pointer and calls InitPresContextData() to capture the explicit original target. Event::InitEvent() sets bubbles/cancelable flags and clears prior target pointers for re-dispatch.",
